    },
    {
      "id": "DrKDDFvg6tnx0yePBPnps",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1012.415252840214,
      "y": 7556.015474076892,
      "width": 544.5611572265625,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "c0dQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 976218262,
      "version": 1366,
      "versionNonce": 458998646,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783161346429,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Complete the whole functionality of ERC-20 Contract \n2. Add the remaining functions: transferFrom(), approve()\n3. See if I can fetch the details of the 2 mapping: \n    - balanceOf\n    - allowance \n4. Then, I'll be done & moving forward to testing out Hardhat \n    & Foundry with the same project \n\n\nUpdates / Improvements : \n1. Write a single provider instead of having to it separate for every \n    single function\n\n2. Get rid of the window.ethereum error, anytime I try to use it \n    I get an error, everytime I have to write \n    if (!window.ethereum) return \"Metamask not installed!\" \n    I have to use window.ethereum withoutt having to use the above \n    line every-time\n\n3. Why is .find() used? I can't make any sense of it ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Complete the whole functionality of ERC-20 Contract \n2. Add the remaining functions: transferFrom(), approve()\n3. See if I can fetch the details of the 2 mapping: \n    - balanceOf\n    - allowance \n4. Then, I'll be done & moving forward to testing out Hardhat \n    & Foundry with the same project \n\n\nUpdates / Improvements : \n1. Write a single provider instead of having to it separate for every \n    single function\n\n2. Get rid of the window.ethereum error, anytime I try to use it \n    I get an error, everytime I have to write \n    if (!window.ethereum) return \"Metamask not installed!\" \n    I have to use window.ethereum withoutt having to use the above \n    line every-time\n\n3. Why is .find() used? I can't make any sense of it ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
